# Accept a one-time payment

This guide walks through how to process a one-time payment using the Sample Payments Virtual Terminal.

---

## Step 1: Select transaction type

Navigate to the **Take a Payment** tab and select the **Sale** transaction type.

This option allows you to process a one-time payment.

![Select Sale Transaction](/images/virtual-terminal/GUID-3d0c1b50-fa21-4476-9dd8-e6bcc5136d5a.png)
---

## Step 2: Enter sale details

Add relevant sales items using the **Sale Items** dropdown, or enter the total payment amount directly.

This ensures the transaction accurately reflects the items or services provided.

![Select Sale Transaction](/images/virtual-terminal/GUID-d6d6707a-7604-4c9e-9b9e-fb32dba591c2.png)
---

## Step 3: Enter customer and payment information

Provide the customer’s name and payment details.

Make sure all information is accurate before proceeding.

![Select Sale Transaction](/images/virtual-terminal/GUID-6354a15d-7080-4939-8415-05804c28567c.png)
---

## Step 4: Apply additional fields (optional)

Under **Additional Fields**, you can:

- Apply taxes  
- Add discounts  
- Include an order note  

These options allow you to customize the transaction as needed.

![Select Sale Transaction](/images/virtual-terminal/GUID-f2afe2a4-e801-4586-bf29-51efdf776080.png)
---

## Step 5: Review customer information (optional)

Under **Customer Info**, you can:

- View or update customer details  
- Add or edit a shipping address  

This helps ensure accurate recordkeeping and proper customer association.

![Select Sale Transaction](/images/virtual-terminal/GUID-c1d79d8b-4a83-4e72-be3a-48060dc0cb4b.png)
---

## Step 6: Review and submit

Carefully review the transaction summary.

Once all details are confirmed, click **Charge** to complete the payment.

![Select Sale Transaction](/images/virtual-terminal/GUID-8d224718-df25-490c-8713-117ac18932d9.png)